The breakfast was of a high standard - freshly squeezed orange juice, lovely croissant, eggs cooked to order - lots of choice..	The breakfast buffet at the hotel is good - healthy and fresh with plenty of choice, but don't expect service with a smile.	We got a good deal which included breakfast which was fine - plenty of choice, but don't expect anything cooked apart from hard boiled eggs.	I did not try the breakfast, since it was rather expensive (17.50 euro), and there were nice bakeries right around the corner.